description:
&lt;p&gt;Stroke is the leading cause of death and disability in the UK with more first time strokes occurring at an earlier age compared to 10 years ago (Gov.UK, 2018). Stroke can be a life changing event for the patient and their families.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Our established Stroke unit consists of 21 beds, 17 beds and a 4 bedded Acute Stroke Unit . We are committed to delivering the best care to not only our patients but also to their families, supporting them through what can be a traumatic event.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are looking for dedicated nurses to join our team who are passionate about delivering the best care possible, who have excellent communications skills and are willing to work as part of a committed and skilled multi disciplinary team, striving to achieve the best possible outcome for our patients and their families. Stroke is a specialized area and the applicant will need to have an interest in Stroke.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; There will be ample opportunities to develop your knowledge in both the acute side of stroke and the continuing rehabilitation process.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Support will be given from all team members during your transition onto the ward.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; There are both full and part time posts available, this will be on a shift working pattern including days and nights. There is also the option of long day shifts.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Newly qualified nurses are also welcome to apply, we have an extensive Preceptorship programme for all newly qualified or Return to practice nurses.There is also the option of a rotation between different wards within the Hospital.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you feel you have the qualities and commitment to join this unique and specialised team then please feel free to contact the Ward Manager Rachel Owen with any questions on 01437 773911.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
